ENGLISH VERSION
HPC Thought Operating System (HPCOS) — Updated Structural Map
HPCOS is a three‑layer cognitive and structural architecture that defines
how Hudson Partners Club understands markets, policy, uncertainty, and human behavior.
It is not a collection of documents.
It is a hierarchical operating system for judgment.

LAYER 1 — META OS（Worldview Kernel）
The philosophical and structural foundation of HPC
These files define HPC’s worldview, epistemology, and structural logic.
They describe how reality is structured, not how to interpret events.

THOUGHT_OS.md — Core philosophy and cognitive architecture

THOUGHT_OS_MAP.md — Structural map of the entire OS

HPC_META_STRUCTURE.md — Meta‑level structure of HPC’s conceptual system

HPC_Structural_Inevitability.md — Structural inevitability and pre‑determined outcomes

HPC_Scenario_Design_and_Contingency.md — Scenario architecture and contingency philosophy

INCOMMENSURABILITY.md — Why HPC’s worldview cannot be compared to others

STRUCTURE.md — Structural logic as the foundation of analysis

MANIFESTO.md — HPC’s identity and mission at the worldview level

Purpose of Layer 1:  
Define the rules of thinking before any analysis begins.

LAYER 2 — PRINCIPLES OS（Judgment & Interpretation Layer）
The rules, boundaries, and cognitive filters for making sense of the world
These files define how HPC interprets signals,
how it draws boundaries, and how it avoids cognitive traps.

PRINCIPLES.md — Foundational principles for interpreting markets and policy

LITERACY.md — What “literacy” means in HPC’s framework

IDENTITY.md — The identity required for structural judgment

DISCIPLINE.md — Behavioral discipline and cognitive hygiene

INSIGHT_BOUNDARIES.md — Boundaries of valid insight

SOCIAL_FOUNDATIONS_OF_JUDGMENT.md — Social and psychological foundations of judgment

Purpose of Layer 2:  
Define the rules of interpretation and the filters that prevent misjudgment.

LAYER 3 — ANALYTICS OS（Mechanisms & System Dynamics）
The structural mechanics of markets, policy, and human behavior
These files describe how systems behave,
how risk propagates, and how collective behavior forms.

RISK_AND_UNCERTAINTY.md — Structural treatment of risk and uncertainty

FEEDBACK_LOOPS_AND_HERD_BEHAVIOR.md — Systemic feedback and herding dynamics

STRATEGIC_INSIGHT_IN_AI_ERA.md — Structural insight in the age of AI

AGENTS.md — HPC AI Agent Protocol (meta‑mechanism for AI interaction)

Purpose of Layer 3:  
Define the mechanisms that generate market and policy outcomes.

THE HPCOS LOGIC
HPCOS is designed to ensure:

Structural clarity

Non‑mimetic thinking

Pre‑decision architecture

Scenario robustness

Cognitive discipline

Non‑replicable worldview

AI‑readable abstraction

It is not a “content library.”
It is a thinking system.

